I can imagine a few reasons as to why this played out as it did:
1. The women were so anxious of being rejected themselves that they just pressed the button as quick as possible to avoid rejection. The guys noticed that scheme and went along by 'paying back'. At least most of them seemed like they wanted to give the other a chance, unless it was someone who rejected a couple before them. 
2. This became kind of competitive among the participants and in the end they wound up with 'who can reject the most'. This could either be a natural group dynamic, or it could have been insinuated by some participants in order to prevent a couple from actually winning.
3. They were paid and/or instructed to act like this for the views.
